@graph.rdfs:label: 'abnormal traffic'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A traffic condition which is not normal.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'accepted payment cards'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Use this class to describe details in case acceptedMeansOfPayment is set to 'paymentCard'.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'accident'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Accidents are events where one or more vehicles are involved in collisions or in leaving the roadway. These include collisions between vehicles or with other road users or obstacles.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'activity'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Deliberate human action external to the traffic stream or roadway which could disrupt traffic.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'affected carriageway and lanes'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Supplementary positional information which details carriageway and lane locations. Several instances may exist where the element being described extends over more than one carriageway.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c area'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An area defined by reference to a predefined ALERT-C location table.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c direction'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The direction of traffic flow along the road to which the information relates.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c linear'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear section along a road defined between two points on the road by reference to a pre-defined ALERT-C location table.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c linear by code'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear section along a road defined by reference to a linear section in a pre-defined ALERT-C location table.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c location'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Identification of a specific point, linear or area location in an ALERT-C location table.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c method to linear'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear section along a road between two points, Primary and Secondary, which are pre-defined in an ALERT-C location table. Direction is FROM the Secondary point TO the Primary point, i.e. the Primary point is downstream of the Secondary point.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c method to point'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A single point on the road network defined by reference to a point in a pre-defined ALERT-C location table and which has an associated direction of traffic flow.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c method to primary point location'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The point (called Primary point) which is either a single point or at the downstream end of a linear road section. The point is specified by a reference to a point in a pre-defined ALERT-C location table.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c method to secondary point location'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The point (called Secondary point) which is at the upstream end of a linear road section. The point is specified by a reference to a point in a pre-defined ALERT-C location table.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c method for linear'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear section along a road between two points, Primary and Secondary, which are pre-defined ALERT-C locations plus offset distance. Direction is FROM the Secondary point TO the Primary point, i.e. the Primary point is downstream of the Secondary point.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c method for point'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A single point on the road network defined by reference to a point in a pre-defined ALERT-C location table plus an offset distance and which has an associated direction of traffic flow.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c method for primary point location'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The point (called Primary point) which is either a single point or at the downstream end of a linear road section. The point is specified by a reference to a point in a pre-defined ALERT-C location table plus a non-negative offset distance.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c method for secondary point location'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The point (called Secondary point) which is at the upstream end of a linear road section. The point is specified by a reference to a point in a pre-defined Alert-C location table plus a non-negative offset distance.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'alert c point'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A single point on the road network defined by reference to a pre-defined ALERT-C location table and which has an associated direction of traffic flow.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'animal presence obstruction'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An obstruction on the road resulting from the presence of animals.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'application rate value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of the application rate of a substance.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'area'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A geographic or geometric defined area which may be qualified by height information to provide additional geospatial discrimination (e.g. for snow in an area but only above a certain altitude).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'area destination'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The specification of the destination of a defined route or itinerary which is an area.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'area extended'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Extension class for area used in parking publication extension.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'authority operation'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Authority initiated operation or activity that could disrupt traffic.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'axle flow value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of the flow rate of vehicle axles.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'axle spacing'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The spacing details between the axle sets of an individual vehicle numbered from the front to the back of the vehicle. '@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'axle weight'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The weight details of a specific axle on the vehicle. '@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'basic data'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Data that is either measured or calculated (elaborated) at the same time or over the same time period.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'car parks'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Provides information on the status of one or more car parks.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'catalogue reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Identification of the supplier's data catalogue in a data exchange context.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'cause'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Contains details of the cause of a record within a situation'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'charge'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A particular charge for a specified interval belonging a charge band.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'charge band'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A charge band in accordance with the specified conditions, possibly up to a maximum duration, during a specified period and for a vehicle of specified characteristics (in case of parking).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'charge band by reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Using (a) prior defined charge band(s), identified by its reference.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'comment'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A free text comment with an optional date/time stamp that can be used by the operator to convey un-coded observations/information.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'concentration of vehicles value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of the concentration of vehicles on a unit stretch of road in a given direction.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'conditions'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Any conditions which have the potential to degrade normal driving conditions.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'contact'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Address and contact information about some person, service or the parking site, provided in detail or via reference.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'contact by reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Contact information that is addressed via a reference.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'contact details'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Details for some person, service or the parking site itself, especially address information.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'D2 logical model'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The DATEX II logical model comprising exchange, content payload and management sub-models.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'data value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A data value of something that can be measured or calculated. Any provided meta-data values specified in the attributes override any specified generic characteristics such as defined for a specific measurement in the MeasurementSiteTable. '@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'date time value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of an instance in time.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'day week month'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Specification of periods defined by the intersection of days, weeks and months.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'dedicated access'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Reference to an access of any type (vehicles, pedestrian.).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'delays'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The details of the delays being caused by the situation element defined in the situation record. It is recommended to only use one of the optional attributes to avoid confusion.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'destination'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The specification a destination. This may be either a point location or an area location.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'dimension'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A component that provides dimension information. The product of width and height must not be necessarily be the square footage (e.g. in multi-storey buildings or when some zones are not part of the square footage).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'direction bearing value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of direction as a bearing.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'direction compass value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of direction as a point of the compass.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'distance along linear element'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Distance of a point along a linear element either measured from the start node or a defined referent on that linear element, where the start node is relative to the element definition rather than the direction of traffic flow.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'distance from linear element referent'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Distance of a point along a linear element measured from a 'from referent' on the linear element, in the sense relative to the linear element definition rather than the direction of traffic flow or optionally towards a 'towards referent'.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'distance from linear element start'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Distance of a point along a linear element measured from the start node of the linear element, where start node is relative to the element definition rather than the direction of traffic flow.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'disturbance activity'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Deliberate human action of either a public disorder nature or of a situation alert type which could disrupt traffic.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'elaborated data'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An instance of data which is derived/computed from one or more measurements over a period of time. It may be a current value or a forecast value predicted from historical measurements.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'elaborated data fault'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Details of a fault which is being reported for the related elaborated data.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'elaborated data publication'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A publication containing one or more elaborated data sets.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'electric charging'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Additional information for the equipment 'electricChargingStation'. This component refers to the number of charging stations specified in the attribute 'numberOfEquipmentOrServiceFacilities'.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'environmental obstruction'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An obstruction on the road resulting from an environmental cause.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'equipment or system fault'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Equipment or system which is faulty, malfunctioning or not in a fully operational state that may be of interest or concern to road operators and road users.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'exchange'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Details associated with the management of the exchange between the supplier and the client.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'external referencing'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A location defined by reference to an external/other referencing system.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'fault'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Information about a fault relating to a specific piece of equipment or process.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'filter exit management'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Filter indicators management information.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'filter reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Details of a supplier's filter in a data exchange context.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'floating point metre distance value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of distance in metres in a floating point format.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'general instruction or message to road users'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'General instruction and/or message that is issued by the network/road operator which is applicable to drivers and sometimes passengers.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'general network management'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Network management action that is instigated either manually or automatically by the network/road operator. Compliance with any resulting control may be advisory or mandatory.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'generic situation record'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A generic SituationRecord for use when adding level B extensions at the SituationRecord level.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'gross weight characteristic'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Gross weight characteristic of a vehicle.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'group of locations'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'One or more physically separate locations. Multiple locations may be related, as in an itinerary (or route), or may be unrelated. It is not for identifying the same physical location using different Location objects for different referencing systems.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'group of parking sites'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A logical composition of parking sites with aggregated properties (e.g. number of spaces). Examples: Urban parking area 'West' or all truck parkings along a motorway. The included parking sites may -but must not- be specified as subcomponents.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'group of parking sites status'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Dynamic status information for the static object 'GroupOfParkingSites'.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'group of parking spaces'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A group of parking spaces. All information provided has to be identical for all places in this group. Can also be used just to give the number of lorry parkings, for example. 'GroupOfParkingSpaces' may be multiple defined or include each other.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'group of parking spaces status'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The status of the assigned parking spaces in the specified parking site, i.e. the status of those spaces assigned for particular types of person or vehicle and/or for specific duration types (e.g. short stay).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'group of people involved'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Group of people involved in the event having common characteristics and/or status.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'group of vehicles involved'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Group of the vehicles involved having common characteristics and/or status.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'hazardous materials'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Details of hazardous materials.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'header information'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Management information relating to the data contained within a publication.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'heaviest axle weight characteristic'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Weight characteristic of the heaviest axle on the vehicle.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'height characteristic'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Height characteristic of a vehicle.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'humidity'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Details of atmospheric humidity.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'humidity information'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Measurements of atmospheric humidity.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'impact'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An assessment of the impact that an event or operator action defined by the situation record has on the driving conditions.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'individual charge'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Information on the individual charge for parking the specified vehicle.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'individual vehicle data values'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Measured or calculated data values relating to individual vehicles derived from detectors at the specified measurement site.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'infrastructure damage obstruction'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An obstruction on the road resulting from the failure or damage of infrastructure on, under, above or close to the road.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'inter urban parking site'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A parking site in an interurban context.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'international identifier'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An identifier/name whose range is specific to the particular country.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'itinerary'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Multiple (i.e. more than one) physically separate locations arranged as an ordered set that defines an itinerary or route.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'itinerary by indexed locations'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Multiple physically separate locations arranged as an ordered set that defines an itinerary or route. The index qualifier indicates the order.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'itinerary by reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Multiple (i.e. more than one) physically separate locations which are ordered that constitute an itinerary or route where they are defined by reference to a predefined itinerary.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'junction'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Junction (on a highway), can also be an interchange or if applicable also a motorway service station (see junctionClassification).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'kilograms concentration value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of concentration of a substance in grams per unit volume.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'length characteristic'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Length characteristic of a vehicle.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'life cycle management'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Information relating to the life cycle management of the situation record.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'linear'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear section along a single road with optional directionality defined between two points on the same road. '@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'linear element'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear element along a single linear object, consistent with ISO 19148 definitions. '@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'linear element by code'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear element along a single linear object defined by its identifier or code in a road network reference model (specified in LinearElement class) which segments the road network according to specific business rules.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'linear element by points'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear element along a single linear object defined by its start and end points.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'linear traffic view'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An identifiable instance of a linear traffic view at a single point in time relating to a linear section of road, comprising one or more traffic view records.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'linear within linear element'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A linear section along a linear element where the linear element is either a part of or the whole of a linear object (i.e. a road), consistent with ISO 19148 definitions. '@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'location'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The specification of a location either on a network (as a point or a linear location) or as an area. This may be provided in one or more referencing systems.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'location by reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A location defined by reference to a predefined location.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'location characteristics override'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Location characteristics which override values set in the referenced measurement point.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'maintenance vehicles'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Details of the maintenance vehicles involved in the roadworks activity.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'maintenance works'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Roadworks involving the maintenance or installation of infrastructure.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'managed cause'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A cause of this situation record which is managed by the publication creator, i.e. one which is represented by another situation record produced by the same publication creator.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'management'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Information relating to the management of the situation record.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'measured data publication'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A publication containing one or more measurement data sets, each set being measured at a single measurement site.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'measured value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Contains optional characteristics for the specific measured value (indexed to correspond with the defined characteristics of the measurement at the referenced measurement site) which override the static characteristics defined in the MeasurementSiteTable.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'measurement equipment fault'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Details of a fault which is being reported for the related measurement equipment.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'measurement site record'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An identifiable single measurement site entry/record in the Measurement Site table.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'measurement site table'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A Measurement Site Table comprising a number of sets of data, each describing the location from where a stream of measured data may be derived. Each location is known as a 'measurement site' which can be a point, a linear road section or an area.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'measurement site table publication'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A publication containing one or more Measurment Site Tables.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'measurement specific characteristics'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Characteristics which are specific to an individual measurement type (specified in a known order) at the given measurement site.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'micrograms concentration value'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A measured or calculated value of concentration of a substance in micrograms per unit volume.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'mobility'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An indication of whether the associated instance of a SituationRecord is mobile (e.g. a march or parade moving along a road) or stationary.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'named area'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'An area defined by a name and/or in terms of known boundaries, such as country or county boundaries or allocated control area of particular authority. The attributes do not form a union, instead, the smallest intersection forms the resulting area.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'network location'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The specification of a location on a network (as a point or a linear location).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'network management'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Network management action which is applicable to the road network and its users.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'non ordered location group by list'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A group of (i.e. more than one) physically separate locations which have no specific order and where each location is explicitly listed.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'non ordered location group by reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A group of (i.e. more than one) physically separate locations which have no specific order that are defined by reference to a predefined non ordered location group.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'non ordered locations'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Multiple (i.e. more than one) physically separate locations which have no specific order.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'non road event information'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Information about an event which is not on the road, but which may influence the behaviour of drivers and hence the characteristics of the traffic flow.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'non weather related road conditions'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Road surface conditions that are not related to the weather but which may affect driving conditions.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'number of axles characteristic'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Number of axles characteristic of a vehicle.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'obstruction'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Any stationary or moving obstacle of a physical nature (e.g. obstacles or vehicles from an earlier accident, shed loads on carriageway, rock fall, abnormal or dangerous loads, or animals etc.) which could disrupt or endanger traffic.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'offset distance'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The non negative offset distance from the ALERT-C referenced point to the actual point.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'opening times'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A specification of opening times (e.g. for a parking site, a service facility, an access or the availability for equipment).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR area location reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'a two-dimensional part of the surface of the earth which is bounded by a closed curve. An area location may cover parts of the road network but does not necessarily need to. It is represente according to the OpenLR standard for Area Locations'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR base location reference point'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Base class used to hold data about a reference point.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR base point location'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Holds common data that are used both in OpenlrPointAccessPoint and OpenlrPointAlongLine.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR circle location reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'the openLR method of areadefinition by providing a center position and a radius'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR closed line location reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'the openLR method of areadefinition by providing a closed path (i.e. a circuit) in the road network. The boundary always consists of road segments'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR extended area'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Extension to provide Area information in openLR format'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR extended linear'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Extension class for OpenLR Line location reference'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR extended point'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Extension class for OpenLR point.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR geo coordinate'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A geo-coordinate pair is a position in a map defined by its longitude and latitude coordinate values.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR grid attributes'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'attributes required for the grid method'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR grid location reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'the openLR method of areadefinition by providing repeating rectangles'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR last location reference point'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The sequence of location reference points is terminated by a last location reference point.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR line attributes'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Line attributes are part of a location reference point and consists of functional road class (FRC),form of way (FOW) and bearing (BEAR) data.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR line location reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A LineLocationReference is defined by an ordered sequence of location reference points and a terminating last location reference point.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR location reference point'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The basis of a location reference is a sequence of location reference points (LRPs).'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR offsets'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Offsets are used to locate the start and end of a location more precisely than bounding to the nodes in a network.'@en

@graph.rdfs:comment: 'The field path attributes is part of a location reference point (except for the last location reference point) and consists of lowest functional road class (LFRCNP) and distance to next point (DNP) data.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR poi with access point'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Point along line with access is a point location which is defined by a line,an offset value and a coordinate.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR point along line'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'Point along a line'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR point location reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'A point location is a zero-dimensional element in a map that specifies a geometric location.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR polygon corners'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'geo-coordinate pairs. The coordinate pairs defining the corners of the underlying geometrical polygon.'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR polygon location reference'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'the openLR method of areadefinition by providing points that bound the area'@en

@graph.rdfs:label: 'openLR rectangle'@en
@graph.rdfs:comment: 'two geo-coordinate pairs defining the rectangular'@en
